<recipe lang="en-uk" xmlns:lxslt="http://xml.apache.org/xslt">
<title><![CDATA[Beef, Tea and Chicory Thai Curry]]></title>
<description><![CDATA[Originally made with cassia leaves, which need blanchin 3-5 times from a cold start. Go well with pickled red shallots, steamed eggs, and grilled fish]]></description>
<source/>
<img></img>
<cuisine>
<style>Thai</style>
<region/>
<approach/>
</cuisine>
<tags>
<tag>With rice</tag>
<tag/>
</tags>
<directions xmlns:php="http://php.net/xsl">&gt;
<step><![CDATA[Make curry paste by putting all ingredients one by one in mortar, or food processor]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Grill the beef until rare on both sides and set aside]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Reduce coconut cream, 5 or 6 mins stirring regularly, then add 3 tbsp curry paste, 6/7 mins.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Add the palm sugar, a few minutes until darkened, and the fish sauce, a few more minutes]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Add the coconut milk / stock, and the tea.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Slice the beef, ginger, and chicory. and add to the curry with lime leaves]]></step>
&gt;</directions>
